VALUES
(56, 1, 1, 45, 1, 1, 1, 'a servant of God, and an apostle', 'Connection of Apostolic Identity', 'Both passages emphasize Paul’s role as a servant and apostle. They highlight his dedication to the gospel and the faith of God''s elect.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 1, 54, 6, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Godliness in Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doctrine that is ''according to godliness.'' This connection highlights a shared focus on the truth and teachings that align with a godly life.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 1, 55, 2, 23, 23, 'acknowledging of the truth', 'Avoiding Strife and Acknowledging Truth', 'This connection highlights the importance of acknowledging truth in faith while avoiding foolish disputes that lead to strife. Both passages emphasize the need for discernment in discussions related to godliness and truth.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 1, 56, 2, 11, 12, 'which is after godliness', 'Connection of Godliness and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of godliness in the life of believers. The acknowledgment of truth in Titus 1:1 leads to the teaching of living godly in Titus 2:11-12, illustrating a progression from faith to practice.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 1, 61, 1, 3, 3, 'godliness', 'Connection of Godliness in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of godliness as essential to the believer''s life. Titus speaks of the truth which is after godliness, while 2 Peter mentions all things that pertain unto life and godliness.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 1, 51, 2, 2, 2, 'acknowledging of the truth', 'Connection of Acknowledgment and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of acknowledgment in relation to faith and understanding. Titus speaks of the ''acknowledging of the truth,'' while Colossians refers to the ''acknowledgement of the mystery of God.''', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 1, 53, 2, 13, 14, 'the faith of God’s elect', 'Connection of Election and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being chosen by God and the importance of truth in faith. Titus speaks of the ''faith of God’s elect,'' while 2 Thessalonians mentions being ''chosen...through sanctification of the Spirit and belief of the truth.''', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 2, 4, 23, 19, 19, 'God, that cannot lie', 'God''s Truthfulness and Promises', 'Both passages emphasize that God cannot lie, highlighting His faithfulness to His promises. Titus 1:2 speaks of God''s promise of eternal life, while Numbers 23:19 asserts that God does not lie or change His mind.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 2, 55, 1, 9, 9, 'before the world began', 'Eternal Life and Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize concepts of eternal life and divine purpose given before the world began. They highlight God''s promises and grace as foundational to salvation.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 2, 62, 2, 25, 25, 'eternal life', 'Promise of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of eternal life. Titus 1:2 mentions this promise made by God, while 1 John 2:25 directly states that this is the promise given to believers.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 2, 58, 6, 17, 18, 'which God, that cannot lie, promised', 'Promise of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize God''s inability to lie, highlighting the certainty of His promises. The assurance of eternal life in Titus connects with the immutability of God''s counsel in Hebrews, reinforcing the hope believers have in His promises.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 2, 62, 5, 11, 13, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Life Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of eternal life from God. Titus highlights God''s unchanging promise, while 1 John assures believers of their possession of eternal life through the Son.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 2, 9, 15, 29, 29, 'God, that cannot lie', 'God''s Nature of Truthfulness', 'Both passages emphasize that God cannot lie, highlighting His unchanging nature. This connection underscores the reliability of God''s promises and His divine character.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 2, 55, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of Eternal Life Promises', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of life, linking eternal life in Titus with the promise of life in Christ in 2 Timothy. This connection highlights the continuity of God''s promise throughout the New Testament.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 3, 54, 1, 11, 11, 'committed unto me according to the commandment', 'Connection of Gospel Commitment', 'Both passages emphasize the commitment of the gospel. Titus 1:3 mentions the preaching committed according to God''s command, while 1 Timothy 1:11 refers to the gospel committed to Paul''s trust.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 3, 54, 1, 1, 1, 'commandment of God our Saviour', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Paul as an apostle through the commandment of God our Saviour. This connection highlights the divine commissioning that underpins Paul''s ministry in both letters.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 3, 56, 3, 4, 6, 'God our Saviour', 'Connection of God''s Kindness', 'Both passages emphasize the role of God our Saviour in revealing His mercy and salvation. The manifestation of His word in preaching connects to the kindness and love that appeared through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 3, 56, 2, 10, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Doctrine and Fidelity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the doctrine of God our Saviour. The preaching in Titus 1:3 is linked to the good fidelity in Titus 2:10, suggesting that faithful living adorns this doctrine.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 3, 23, 45, 15, 15, 'God our Saviour', 'Connection of God''s Manifestation', 'This connection highlights the theme of God as Saviour. Both passages refer to God revealing Himself, with Titus emphasizing the manifestation of His word and Isaiah acknowledging God as the hidden Saviour.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 3, 23, 45, 21, 21, 'God our Saviour', 'Manifestation of God as Saviour', 'This connection highlights the theme of God revealing His word and identity as Saviour. Both passages emphasize God''s role in declaring His truth and salvation to humanity.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 3, 45, 10, 14, 15, 'through preaching', 'Connection of Preaching and Belief', 'This connection highlights the importance of preaching in facilitating belief. Both passages emphasize that the word of God is manifested through preaching, which is essential for people to hear and believe.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 4, 55, 1, 2, 2, 'Grace, mercy, and peace', 'Grace, Mercy, and Peace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a shared greeting structure in the letters to Titus and Timothy.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 4, 65, 1, 3, 3, 'common faith', 'Common Faith and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of ''common faith'' and ''common salvation'' in both passages. Both Titus and Jude emphasize the importance of faith within the Christian community.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 4, 47, 2, 13, 13, NULL, 'Connection through Titus', 'Both passages emphasize the figure of Titus, highlighting his importance in the early church. In Titus 1:4, he is referred to as a son in faith, while in 2 Corinthians 2:13, Paul expresses concern for him as a brother.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 4, 61, 1, 1, 1, 'common faith', 'Faith and Salvation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of faith, referring to it as ''common faith'' in Titus and ''like precious faith'' in 2 Peter. They also highlight the role of Jesus Christ as Saviour, linking the believers'' faith to His righteousness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 4, 61, 1, 11, 11, 'our Saviour', 'Connection of Salvation Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus Christ as Saviour, highlighting the importance of grace and the promise of an everlasting kingdom. This connection underscores the assurance of salvation and the relationship believers have with Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 4, 43, 4, 42, 42, 'our Saviour', 'Connection of Saviour References', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus as ''Saviour.'' Titus refers to Jesus as ''our Saviour,'' while John identifies Him as ''the Saviour of the world.'' This connection highlights the shared recognition of Jesus'' role in salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 4, 45, 1, 12, 12, 'common faith', 'Connection of Mutual Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of mutual faith among believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of faith in fostering relationships within the Christian community.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 5, 44, 14, 23, 23, 'ordain elders in every city', 'Elders in Every City/Church', 'This connection highlights the theme of ordaining elders in multiple locations. Both passages emphasize the establishment of church leadership in various communities.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 5, 54, 1, 3, 3, 'ordain elders in every city', 'Leadership and Teaching Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of establishing leadership within the church. Both passages emphasize the importance of appointing elders and charging leaders to maintain sound doctrine.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 5, 21, 12, 9, 9, 'set in order', 'Wisdom and Order in Teaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of setting things in order and the importance of wise teaching. Both passages emphasize the role of leadership in organizing knowledge and guiding the community.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 5, 46, 14, 40, 40, 'set in order the things that are wanting', 'Order in Church Leadership', 'This connection highlights the importance of establishing order within the church. Both passages emphasize the necessity of doing things ''decently and in order'' as well as setting ''in order the things that are wanting.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 5, 23, 44, 7, 7, 'set in order', 'Order and Appointment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of setting things in order and the appointment of leaders. Both passages emphasize the act of establishing order and authority within a community, reflecting God''s intention in governance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 5, 44, 11, 30, 30, 'ordain elders in every city', 'Connection of Elders in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the role of elders in the early church. Titus is instructed to ordain elders, while Acts mentions sending aid to the elders, highlighting their importance in church governance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 5, 46, 11, 34, 34, 'set in order', 'Order and Organization in Church', 'This connection highlights the theme of setting things in order within the church. Both passages emphasize the need for proper organization and structure in the community of believers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 6, 54, 3, 2, 7, 'blameless, the husband of one wife', 'Qualifications for Church Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the requirement of being blameless and the husband of one wife, highlighting the importance of personal integrity and family management for church leaders. They also stress the necessity of ruling one''s household well as a reflection of one''s ability to lead the church.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 6, 54, 3, 12, 12, 'the husband of one wife', 'Qualifications for Church Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being ''the husband of one wife'' and managing one''s household well. This connection highlights the qualifications necessary for church leaders, specifically regarding family responsibilities.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 6, 56, 1, 6, 8, 'If any be blameless', 'Qualifications for Church Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the need for blamelessness and moral integrity in church leaders. The qualities listed in the target passage build upon the foundational requirement of being ''blameless'' and having ''faithful children.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 6, 3, 21, 7, 7, 'blameless, the husband of one wife', 'Qualifications for Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of moral integrity in leadership roles. Titus highlights the need for a blameless husband, while Leviticus stresses the holiness required in a priest''s marital choices.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 6, 20, 28, 7, 7, 'riot or unruly', 'Connection of Riot and Blamelessness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of avoiding riotous behavior. In Titus, having ''faithful children not accused of riot'' aligns with Proverbs'' warning against being a ''companion of riotous men.'' This connection highlights the value of maintaining a blameless reputation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 6, 26, 44, 22, 22, 'husband of one wife', 'Marriage and Leadership Standards', 'This connection highlights the standards for marriage in leadership roles. Both passages emphasize the importance of marital fidelity and the selection of appropriate spouses.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 6, 49, 5, 18, 18, NULL, 'Spiritual Conduct and Family Life', 'This connection highlights the importance of self-control and responsibility in both passages. While Titus emphasizes being blameless and having faithful children, Ephesians warns against excess, suggesting that spiritual integrity influences family dynamics.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 7, 49, 5, 18, 18, 'not given to wine', 'Connection on Wine and Conduct', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of avoiding drunkenness. Titus warns against being ''given to wine,'' while Ephesians advises not to be ''drunk with wine.'' This connection highlights a shared theme of self-control and spiritual focus.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 7, 61, 2, 10, 10, 'selfwilled', 'Self-willed Leadership Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the trait of being ''selfwilled.'' Titus describes the qualities of a bishop, while 2 Peter warns against those who are selfwilled and despise authority. This connection highlights contrasting attitudes towards leadership and governance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 7, 60, 4, 10, 10, 'steward of God', 'Stewardship in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the role of stewardship, highlighting the responsibility of leaders and believers to manage God''s gifts faithfully. The concept of being a ''steward'' connects the qualifications for bishops in Titus with the call to minister grace in 1 Peter.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 7, 60, 5, 2, 2, 'not given to filthy lucre', 'Leadership Qualities in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not being motivated by ''filthy lucre'' in church leadership. They highlight the need for bishops and elders to lead with integrity and a willing spirit.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 7, 42, 12, 42, 42, 'steward of God', 'Stewardship and Responsibility', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a steward, highlighting the qualities necessary for effective leadership. Titus outlines the character traits of a bishop as a steward of God, while Luke describes a faithful steward entrusted with responsibilities.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 7, 59, 1, 19, 20, 'not soon angry', 'Connection of Conduct and Anger', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of self-control and the avoidance of anger. Titus 1:7 advises against being ''not soon angry,'' while James 1:19-20 encourages being ''slow to wrath.'' This connection highlights the shared theme of righteous behavior.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 7, 20, 14, 17, 17, 'not soon angry', 'Anger and Wisdom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of controlling anger. Titus warns against being ''soon angry,'' while Proverbs states that those who are ''soon angry dealeth foolishly.'' This connection highlights the value of self-control in leadership and wisdom.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 8, 54, 3, 2, 2, NULL, 'Qualifications for Church Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize qualities required for church leaders, such as being ''sober'' and ''given to hospitality.'' This connection highlights the importance of moral character and relational skills in leadership roles.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 8, 56, 2, 7, 7, 'lover of good men', 'Connection of Good Works', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being a ''lover of good men'' and showing ''a pattern of good works.'' This connection highlights the call for moral integrity and positive influence in the community.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 8, 11, 5, 7, 7, 'lover of good men', 'Hospitality and Wisdom Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom and good character. In Titus, the qualities of a leader include being a lover of good men, while in 1 Kings, Hiram rejoices in Solomon''s wisdom, indicating a positive relationship with good leadership.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 8, 9, 18, 1, 1, 'lover of good men', 'Connection of Love and Goodness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love, with Titus highlighting a ''lover of good men'' and 1 Samuel depicting Jonathan''s deep love for David. This connection highlights the importance of loving relationships among individuals who embody goodness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 8, 11, 5, 1, 1, 'lover of good men', 'Connection of Hospitality and Love', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love, with Titus highlighting a ''lover of good men'' and 1 Kings noting Hiram as ''a lover of David.'' This connection highlights the value of relationships and hospitality in leadership.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 8, 19, 16, 3, 3, 'lover of good men', 'Connection of Saints and Goodness', 'Both passages emphasize the value of goodness and excellence in people. Titus highlights being a lover of good men, while Psalms expresses delight in the excellent.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 8, 47, 6, 4, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Character Traits', 'Both passages emphasize qualities of integrity and virtue. Titus 1:8 lists traits like ''sober'' and ''just,'' while 2 Corinthians 6:4-8 highlights ''pureness'' and ''kindness,'' showcasing the moral character expected of God''s ministers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 9, 53, 2, 15, 15, NULL, 'Holding Fast to Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of holding fast to teachings received, whether through sound doctrine or traditions. This connection highlights the necessity of steadfastness in faith and the transmission of teachings.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 9, 55, 1, 13, 13, NULL, 'Connection of Sound Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of holding fast to sound doctrine. They encourage believers to maintain the teachings received, which is essential for effective exhortation and faith.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 9, 54, 6, 3, 3, 'sound doctrine', 'Connection of Sound Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sound doctrine in teaching. Titus 1:9 speaks of holding fast to the faithful word, while 1 Timothy 6:3 warns against teaching otherwise than wholesome words. This connection highlights the necessity of adhering to true teachings.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 9, 54, 1, 10, 10, 'sound doctrine', 'Connection of Sound Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sound doctrine in guiding behavior and addressing false teachings. Titus 1:9 focuses on holding fast to the faithful word, while 1 Timothy 1:10 lists behaviors contrary to sound doctrine.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 9, 66, 3, 3, 3, NULL, 'Holding Fast to Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of holding fast to what has been received and taught. Titus encourages adherence to sound doctrine, while Revelation calls for remembrance and vigilance in faith.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 9, 18, 2, 3, 3, NULL, 'Integrity and Sound Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of holding fast to integrity and sound doctrine. Job''s steadfastness in maintaining his integrity parallels the call in Titus to hold fast the faithful word, suggesting a shared theme of resilience in faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 9, 20, 23, 23, 23, 'the faithful word as he hath been taught', 'Value of Truth and Doctrine', 'This connection highlights the importance of holding onto truth and sound doctrine. Both passages emphasize the necessity of valuing wisdom and understanding, suggesting that truth should be cherished and defended.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 10, 54, 1, 6, 6, 'vain talkers', 'Connection of Vain Talkers', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of ''vain'' speech. Titus mentions ''vain talkers,'' while Timothy refers to ''vain jangling,'' highlighting a shared concern about empty or deceptive communication.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 10, 62, 4, 1, 1, 'deceivers', 'Connection of False Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of deceivers and false prophets. Titus warns about ''vain talkers and deceivers,'' while 1 John advises to ''try the spirits'' due to many false prophets in the world.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 10, 48, 2, 4, 4, 'deceivers', 'False Brethren and Deceivers', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of deceivers among believers. Titus mentions ''vain talkers and deceivers,'' while Galatians refers to ''false brethren'' who seek to undermine faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 10, 49, 4, 14, 14, 'deceivers', 'Connection of Deception and Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of deceivers and the danger of being misled by false teachings. Titus warns against ''vain talkers and deceivers,'' while Ephesians cautions against being ''tossed to and fro'' by deceptive doctrines.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 10, 44, 11, 2, 2, 'they of the circumcision', 'Contention Among Circumcision Group', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of those ''of the circumcision'' who are causing disruption. Titus highlights their deceitful nature, while Acts shows them contending with Peter.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 10, 45, 16, 17, 18, NULL, 'Deception and Division in Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of deceivers who cause divisions among believers. They highlight the danger of those who use persuasive words to mislead others, particularly those who do not adhere to sound doctrine.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 10, 48, 1, 6, 8, 'deceivers', 'Connection of Deception in Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of deceivers who distort the true message of the gospel. Titus warns against ''vain talkers and deceivers,'' while Galatians addresses those who ''pervert the gospel of Christ.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 11, 55, 3, 6, 6, 'subvert whole houses', 'Deceptive Teachings and Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of false teachers who lead others astray. Titus 1:11 mentions those who ''subvert whole houses,'' while 2 Timothy 3:6 describes individuals who ''creep into houses'' and manipulate vulnerable individuals.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 11, 54, 6, 5, 5, 'for filthy lucre’s sake', 'Corruption and False Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of corrupt minds and false teachings that exploit others for personal gain. They warn against those who teach things for ''filthy lucre’s sake'' and suggest that gain is godliness, urging believers to withdraw from such influences.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 11, 45, 3, 19, 19, NULL, 'Stopping of Mouths Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of silencing those who speak falsely. Both passages emphasize the need to stop mouths, whether to prevent subversion or to establish guilt before God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 11, 56, 3, 10, 10, 'teaching things which they ought not', 'Rejection of False Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the need to address false teachings. Titus 1:11 warns against those who subvert households, while Titus 3:10 instructs to reject a heretic after admonition.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 11, 19, 63, 11, 11, NULL, 'Stopping False Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the need to silence those who speak lies or teach falsehoods. Titus 1:11 mentions stopping mouths that subvert, while Psalms 63:11 speaks of stopping the mouths of liars.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 11, 56, 1, 9, 9, 'teaching things which they ought not', 'Connection of Doctrine and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sound doctrine in countering false teachings. The first verse warns against those who teach for ''filthy lucre’s sake,'' while the second encourages holding fast to the faithful word to convince gainsayers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 11, 19, 107, 42, 42, NULL, 'Mouths Stopped and Iniquity Silenced', 'This connection highlights the theme of silencing false teachings and iniquity. Both passages emphasize the stopping of mouths, indicating a divine intervention against those who lead others astray.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 12, 45, 16, 18, 18, 'slow bellies', 'Deception and Self-Serving Motives', 'This connection highlights the theme of deception and self-serving behavior. Both passages address individuals who deceive others for their own gain, with Titus mentioning ''slow bellies'' and Romans referring to serving ''their own belly.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(56, 1, 12, 54, 4, 2, 2, 'liars', 'Connection of Deception and Hypocrisy', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of deceit, with Titus referencing ''liars'' and 1 Timothy discussing ''speaking lies in hypocrisy.'' This connection highlights the moral failings attributed to certain groups and individuals.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
